2. Conflux runtime library — a Dafny runtime library providing the reducer kernel
   (ConfluxContract.Fold), the JSON codec (ConfluxCodec), keyed-sequence routing
   primitives (ConfluxSeqRoute), content addressing, and capability seams.

   Copyright (c) 2026 Josh Mouch
   Licensed under the MIT License as part of this distribution.

   DISCLOSURE: Conflux is REDISTRIBUTED INSIDE the published packages. Dafny
   extraction inlines the library into the emitted source, so there is no separate
   Conflux dependency to install — the code is compiled into every artifact:

     Python   agent-host-protocol            49 of 61 modules under _core/
     Go       .../ahp-verified/go            52 of 66 tracked .go files
     JavaScript @open-agency/ahp             48 Conflux modules inside dist/ahp.cjs
     .NET     Ahp.Core.Verified              49 of 72 namespaces in AhpCore.g.cs,
                                             plus 5 Runtime/Conflux*Adapter.cs files
     JVM      agency.open.ahp:ahp-core       25 files across 6 Conflux* packages

   The Conflux source repository is not currently public and, at the time of
   writing, carries no LICENSE file of its own. Because Conflux is the work of
   Josh Mouch, the MIT grant in this repository's LICENSE (under the Josh Mouch
   copyright line) is intended to cover the Conflux code redistributed here.

   The practical consequence for a reader is that the proofs in spec/ cannot be
   re-verified without the Conflux package, which is not published. This is
   documented in full in REPRODUCIBILITY.md, including what that means for the
   "zero owned trusted assumptions" claim.

